Man, wearing orange high-vis jacket, could be seen leaning out of van as it hurtled down the outside lane of the motorway near Oxford .
He appeared to be laughing and making jokes with colleagues inside the van as he hung his body - and even a leg - out of the vehicle .
The incident, which police are investigating, is believed to have gone on for five minutes as the man pulled off the 'stunt' just yards from lorries .